            <entry xml:id="entry_egar" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>egar</orth><form type="variant"
                    >(<orth>jegar</orth>)</form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>борзая собака</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>greyhound dog</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>tar qædy īw sag, pyrx kalgæ jæ ontæj, ūnærǧgæ wadi, — egar æj
                            syrdta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в темном лесу один олень с залитой (кровью) спиной несся с хрипом, —
                                за ним гналась борзая</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>in a dark forest one deer with a (blood-)soaked back rushed with a
                                wheeze, — a greyhound chased after it</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>91</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Erystaw-ældar īw ḱyzg... egaryl awæj kodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Эристав-князь продал одну девушку за борзую собаку</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Eristav the prince sold one girl for a greyhound dog</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Æxsaræ cawæn rajdædta æ duwwæ egarej xæccæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Ахсар стал охотиться со своими двумя борзыми</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Akhsar began to hunt with his two greyhounds</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            7</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>ägar, änär, igar</w>
                        <gloss><q>охотничья собака</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>I 695, 711, 1425</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="cv" extralang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>agár</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>haǵer</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>ier</w></mentioned>. В осетинский слово усвоено скорее всего из
                    старочувашского (булгарского).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>I
                        130</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Jacobsohn"
                            /><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Compare <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>ägar, änär, igar</w>
                        <gloss><q>hunting dog</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>I 695, 711, 1425</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="cv" extralang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>agár</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>haǵer</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>ier</w></mentioned>. Ossetic most likely acquired this word from Old
                    Chuvash (Bulgar).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>I 130</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Jacobsohn"
                    /><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
